      "content": "Research has shown that, statistically speaking, non-white populations are disproportionately represented in crime statistics. Studies have consistently found that African Americans and Hispanics are more likely to be arrested and incarcerated than their white counterparts, with some data suggesting that black Americans are 5-6 times more likely to be incarcerated than whites. Similarly, Native American reservations experience high rates of violent crime, likely due to the historical trauma and systemic oppression faced by these communities. These trends are often attributed to factors such as poverty, lack of access to education and job opportunities, and systemic racism within the justice system.",
